articles.title: The S&P 500 just clinched a fresh all-time high as traders try to spark a Santa Claus rally
articles.mainIdea: The S&P 500 just clinched a fresh all-time high as traders try to spark a Santa Claus rally
articles.summary: Business Insider: The S&P 500 just clinched a fresh all-time high as traders try to spark a Santa Claus rally. The S&P 500 closed at a record high on Tuesday as investors looked to spark a Santa Claus rally in the holiday-shortened trading week.

articles.title: Review & Preview: Next Stop? S&P 7000.
articles.summary: Barrons.com: Review & Preview: Next Stop? S&P 7000.. Thin volume paved the way to another stock market milestone. The Nasdaq Composite rose 0.6%. Only 3.82 billion shares traded on the New York Stock Exchange, which made for the lowest volume day since Jan. 3, according to Dow Jones Market Data.
